Notes: 
* with lyrics 
** with Baker Street (Gerry Rafferty) tease 
^ with Al Schnier (moe.) on guitar 
$ with Cowgirl in the Sand (Neil Young) jam 

More highlights from May bring you a sit-in from Al Schnier, a friend as well as a fan of Umphrey's. The three-pronged guitar attack in the jam out of Much Obliged is a treat. Another vocal &quot;Jimmy Stewart&quot; is followed by the obscure Lounge Lizards' Big Heart, one of the few more straightforward jazz songs that the band attempts. To close out is the 35-minute Nothing Too Fancy excursion that was the highlight of the two week West Coast run for many. It is truly explosive. 


